[[File:Pip-Acolyte.png|thumb|right|250px|PIP droids were a model of handheld repair droid. ]]
'''Maintenance droids''',<ref name="LOS">''[[Lords of the Sith]]''</ref> also known as '''repair droids''',<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars">''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''</ref> '''mechanic droids''',<ref name="Build Your Own R2 1">{{BuildR2Cite|1|Droid Directory}}</ref> '''engineer droids''',<ref name="Chapter 2">{{BOBF|Chapter 2: The Tribes of Tatooine}} Audio description identifies the droid as an engineer droid.</ref> and '''utility robots''',<ref name="DB astromech">{{Databank|astromech-droid|Astromech Droid}}</ref> were [[droid]]s designed to perform repair and general maintenance tasks.<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> Models of repair droids included the [[WED Treadwell repair droid]], the [[MSE-6 series repair droid]],<ref name="AbEverything">''[[Star Wars: Absolutely Everything You Need to Know]]''</ref> the [[DUM-series pit droid]],<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> the [[Otoga-222 maintenance droid]],<ref name="Visual Encyclopedia">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]''</ref> the [[K1-RF workbench droid]],<ref name="TROS Junior">''[[Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker: A Junior Novel]]''</ref> and the [[PIP droid]].<ref name="Pip">{{Databank|pip|Pip}}</ref> 

[[AL-42|One such droid]] had multiple [[limb]]s and operated a [[Tatooine repulsor train|repulsortrain]] operated by the [[Pyke Syndicate]] on [[Tatooine]].<ref name="Chapter 2" />

[[R2-D2]] was one of the [[astromech droid]]s aboard a [[Naboo]] [[J-type 327 Nubian royal starship|royal starship]], was rewarded for emergency maintenance on the [[Starship|ship's]] [[deflector shield]]s, and was the only repair droid to survive the task.<ref name="TPM">{{Film|I}}</ref>

Maintenance droids of the [[Imperial Palace|Jedi Temple]] raked patterns into the gravel floors of the [[Room of a Thousand Fountains]] nightly to replace the ones obliterated by daily foot traffic.<ref name="Trials">''[[The High Republic: Trials of the Jedi]]''</ref>
